==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Torbernite
<hw>Tor"bern*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after
<etsep>Torber</etsep> Bergmann, a Swedish chemist.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring in emerald-green tabular
crystals having a micaceous structure. It is a hydrous phosphate of
uranium and copper. Called also <altname>copper uranite</altname>, and
<altname>chalcolite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Torc</ent>⟦br⟧
